quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,79,""
  37,80,"Verily, thus We reward the Muhsinûn (good-doers - See V.2:112)."
  37,81,"Verily, he [Nûh (Noah)] was one of Our believing slaves."
  38,58,"And other (torments) of similar kind - all together!"
  38,59,"This is a troop entering with you (in Hell), no welcome for them! Verily, they shall burn in the Fire!"
  38,60,"(The followers of the misleaders will say): "
  39,43,"Have they taken (others) as intercessors besides Allâh? Say: "
  39,44,"Say: "
  39,45,"And when Allâh Alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who believe not in the Hereafter are filled with disgust (from the Oneness of Allâh توحيد الله) and when those (whom they obey or worship) besides Him [like all false deities other than Allâh, - it may be a Messenger, an angel, a pious man, a jinni, or any other creature even idols, graves of religious people, saints, priests, monks and others.] are mentioned, behold, they rejoice!{1}",footnotes:1:{39:45} See the footnote of {2:165}.
  40,22,"That was because there came to them their Messengers with clear evidence (proofs and signs) but they disbelieved (in them). So Allâh seized them (with punishment). Verily He is All-Strong, Severe in punishment."
  40,23,"And indeed We sent Mûsâ (Moses) with Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), and a manifest authority,"
  40,24,"To Fir‘aun (Pharaoh), Hâmân and Qârûn (Korah), but they called (him): "
  41,1,"Hâ-Mîm."
  41,2,"A revelation from (Allâh), the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful."
  41,3,"A Book whereof the Verses are explained in detail - a Qur’ân in Arabic for people who know."